Tom, I appreciate the compliments and the "digs" but there is no way I
can help you with your questions. We started working on QUASAR early in
1974. Chuck went on to work on other things sometime around 76-77 and I
moved to a new project (finally) in 1979. At that time I can assure you
that GLXLIB assembled on both operating systems :)..... ORION had just
been released and PULSAR was still under development.

Bottom line is that it is quite likely that I had nothing to do with the
code that was causing you problems and even if I did, it is "at least"
20 years ago and I make it a policy to forget any bugs that I create
after 10 years (Statute of Limitations!).

Regards/lss
